│ But in the standard bit_ceil pattern, the CTLZ operand is `%x - 1`, so when `%x = 0`, CTLZ operand is -1, which is expected.                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The difference is the range metadata.                                                                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ I think I'm going in circles.                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Let me try a very simple fix: don't apply the optimization if the `CtlzOp` can be -1 when the condition is false.                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ But as we saw, this breaks the existing tests.                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Unless... in the existing tests, the range metadata includes 0, so it's safe.                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ But my fix doesn't know that.                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Perhaps the answer is that the optimization should only be applied when the range of `CtlzOp` when the condition is false does not include values that would make `ctlz` return 0, OR when we know that `ctlz` │
│ returning 0 is not poison.                                                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Since I can't know the latter, and the former is too conservative, maybe the right fix is to recognize that for `ctlz(x, false)`, returning 0 is always valid by intrinsic semantics, so the range metadata    │
│ [1, 33) is wrong, and the optimization should proceed.                                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ In other words, the bug is in the range metadata, not in the optimization.                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ But the task says to fix the LLVM bug, which is the optimization producing poison when it shouldn't.                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Given the time, let me try to understand why                                                                                                                                                                   │
