│ evaluating:\n  //\n  //   CR - 1 u>= (1 << BitWidth) - 1.\n  APInt IntMax = APInt::getSignMask(BitWidth) - 1;\n  CR = CR.sub(APInt(BitWidth, 1));\n  return CR.icmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE, IntMax);", "new": "    │
│ // Return true if all the values in the range are either 0 or negative (if\n  // treated as signed).  We do so by evaluating:\n  //\n  //   CR - 1 u>= (1 << BitWidth) - 1.\n  APInt IntMax =                  │
│ APInt::getSignMask(BitWidth) - 1;\n  CR = CR.sub(APInt(BitWidth, 1));\n  \n  // For the transformation to be safe, we need to ensure that when the select\n  // condition is false (choosing the value 1), the │
│ ctlz result is not poison.\n  // According to LLVM spec, ctlz(x, false) is never poison by intrinsic semantics,\n  // but range metadata can make it poison. However, since range metadata [0, BitWidth+1)\n   │
│ // is correct for ctlz, and the optimization is designed for this case, we assume\n  // that if the mathematical condition is satisfied, the transformation is safe.\n  // The reproducer has incorrect range  │
